  "text": "Another method uses the replaceable decentralized consensus protocols commonly used for blockchain IoT networks, named proof-of-stake (PoS) [CITATION_1] . In contrast to PoW, PoS demands much less CPU computation, energy, hardware, etc., in the mining process, and the opportunities for a node to mine the next block are related to the miners account to balance of stakes. The bigger the stake owned by a miner, the more mining power it has.",
